content.description: Use obvious flake that trends SW to NE on slightly overhanging face.  This is a very quick, easy climb that tops out directly above the start.
content.location: It is on the South side of Honeymoon Boulder.

content.description: Start on left side with left hand on left arÃªte and right hand on pinch about waist high.  Put your left foot in a vertical crack in bottom left and a right toe hook in big volleyball-size hole in bottom of rock to keep from barn-dooring.  Move your right hand up to an obvious, two finger pocket.  Cross with your left to a good crimp just NE of the pocket.  Move your right hand to a decent rib running SE diagonal across the face.  Match with left hand on rib, and then do a quick pop up to the lip on natural "V" in top of the rock towards the upper right edge.  Finish out on/around the corner.  The crux is from first two holds to finger pocket.  It is as quick climb (about 6 moves), but it has a good feel and is fun.
content.protection: Nothing really but maybe a pad.
content.location: This is on the East side of Honeymoon Boulder.
